In this essay, Dr. Jill Biden reflects on her son Beau's deployment and the support they received from the community. She shares a prayer that was given to her during Beau's deployment ceremony, expressing her gratitude for the sacrifices made by soldiers. Dr. Biden also discusses the ways in which she and her family stayed connected with Beau during his deployment, such as sending him photos, notes, and care packages. She emphasizes the importance of community support and mentions organizations like Delaware Boots on the Ground, which provides assistance to deployed soldiers and their families. Dr. Biden concludes by expressing her gratitude for Beau's safe return and her commitment to honoring veterans and showing appreciation for their service. She considers herself a member of the military family, even after Beau's deployment.